ns a wage</li>\n  <li>studies - usually 1 day a week - towards a related qualification</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Visit the Skills Development Scotland website for information about <a href=\"http://www.skillsdevelopmentscotland.co.uk/our-services/services-for-individuals/national-training-programmes/modern-apprenticeships.aspx\" title=\"Modern Apprenticeships in Scotland\" rel=\"external\">apprenticeships in Scotland.</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Levels of apprenticeship</h2>\n\n<p>There are 3 levels in England:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>Intermediate – equivalent to 5 GCSE passes</li>\n  <li>Advanced – equivalent to 2 A level passes</li>\n  <li>Higher Apprenticeships – lead to NVQ Level 4 or Foundation Degree</li>\n</ul>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/apprenticeships-guide/what-you-get-as-an-apprentice","slug":"what-you-get-as-an-apprentice","order":2,"title":"What you get as an apprentice","body":"<h2>Pay and holidays</h2>\n\n<p>You&rsquo;ll be paid from the first day of your apprenticeship. The <a href=\"/your-right-to-minimum-wage\" title=\"The National Minimum Wage\">minimum wage</a> for an apprentice is £2.65 per hour and applies to workers aged 16 to 18 and those aged 19 and over in the first year of their apprenticeship. </p>\n\n<p>But many earn more. On average apprentices earn £170 per week and some around £210.</p>\n\n<p>If you&rsquo;re aged 19 or over and have completed the first year of your apprenticeship, you&rsquo;ll be paid at least the <a href=\"/national-minimum-wage-rates\" title=\"National Minimum Wage rates\">National Minimum Wage</a> rate for your age.</p>\n\n<p>Apprentices get at least 20 days of holiday per year, plus bank holidays.</p>\n\n<h2>Qualifications</h2>\n\n<p>Apprenticeships can lead to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>National Vocational Qualifications (NVQs) at Level 2,3,4 or 5</li>\n  <li>Functional Skills qualifications, eg in maths, English or ICT</li>\n  <li>a technical certificate, such as a BTEC or City &amp; Guilds Progression Award</li>\n  <li>knowledge-based qualifications, such as a Higher National Certificate (HNC), a Higher National Diploma (HND) or a Foundation degree</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Types of apprenticeships</h2>\n\n<p>You can find out about the different types of apprenticeships on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.apprenticeships.org.uk/Types-of-Apprenticeships.aspx/\" title=\"Types of apprenticeships\">Apprenticeships</a> website.</p>\n\n<h2>Apply</h2>\n\n<p>Get started and <a href=\"/apply-apprenticeship\" title=\"Apply for an apprenticeship\">apply for an apprenticeship</a>.</p>\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/apprenticeships-guide/taking-on-an-apprentice","slug":"taking-on-an-apprentice","order":3,"title":"Taking on an apprentice","body":"<p>You can use apprenticeships to train both new and existing employees. You can get funding to train apprentices.</p>\n\n<h2>Funding</h2>\n\n<p>The amount of funding you can get for apprenticeship training depends on your sector and the age of your candidate:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>aged 16 to 18 - you get 100% of cost paid</li>\n  <li>aged 19 to 24 - you get 50% of cost paid</li>\n  <li>25 years and older - you may only get a contribution</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>This is paid directly to the organisation that provides and supports the apprenticeship - in most cases the learning provider.</p>\n\n<h2>Apprenticeship grant for employers</h2>\n\n<p>You may also be eligible for a £1,500 <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.apprenticeships.org.uk/Employers/Steps-to-make-it-happen/Incentive.aspx\" title=\"Employer incentive grants\">apprenticeship grant.</a> </p>\n\n<p>These grants are available to help small-medium sized employers to recruit up to 10 apprentices for the first time, and are in addition to the training costs you get for apprentices.</p>\n\n<h2>Take on an apprentice</h2>\n\n<p>Follow the steps on the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.apprenticeships.org.uk/Employers/Steps-to-make-it-happen.aspx\" title=\"Steps to make it happen\">Apprenticeships</a> website to get started, or visit the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.skillsdevelopmentscotland.co.uk/our-services/services-for-employers/modern-apprenticeships.aspx\" title=\"Modern Apprenticeships in Scotland - information for employers\">Skills Development Scotland website</a> if you&rsquo;re in Scotland.</p>\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-11-05T15:02:28+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Finding a job","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ffinding-job.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes job search, volunteering, apprenticeships and job offers","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ffinding-job","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working/finding-job"},"parent":{"title":"Working, jobs and pensions","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes holidays and finding a job","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/working"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Recruiting and hiring","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes discrimination law, apprenticeships and using agencies","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people%2Frecruiting-hiring","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people/recruiting-hiring"},"parent":{"title":"Employing people","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/employing-people.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes pay, contracts and hiring","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=employing-people","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/employing-people"},"parent":null}},{"title":"Apprenticeships,14 