certificate only contains information from a <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> check on a certain date and for a particular purpose. It can be accepted at a later date, but the employer will have to decide if it&rsquo;s recent enough or suitable for the current purpose.</p>\n\n<p>It&rsquo;s also up to the employer to check that the applicant&rsquo;s identity matches the details on the certificate.</p>\n\n<h3>If the applicant loses the certificate</h3>\n\n<p>If the applicant loses the certificate, or it&rsquo;s destroyed, the <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> can&rsquo;t provide a replacement.</p>\n\n<h3>If there&rsquo;s a mistake on the certificate</h3>\n\n<p>If the certificate contains incorrect personal details or criminal record information, the applicant should let the <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> know as soon as possible using the &lsquo;Certificate disputes form&rsquo;.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/CRB/about-the-crb/disputes-form?view=Binary\" title=\"Download 'Certificate disputes form' (PDF, 148KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Certificate disputes form’ (PDF, 148KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<p>The applicant can also <a href=\"/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/contact-criminal-records-bureau\" title=\"contact the CRB\">contact the <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr></a>.</p>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/arranging-crb-checks-as-an-employer","slug":"arranging-crb-checks-as-an-employer","order":4,"title":"Arranging CRB checks as an employer","body":"<p>Employers should only arrange a Criminal Records Bureau (<abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr>) check on a successful job applicant. They can withdraw a job offer if the results show anything that would make the applicant unsuitable.</p>\n\n<p>Employers who need to do fewer than 100 checks a year can use an <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/agencies-public-bodies/crb/about-crb/what-we-do/ub-search/\" title=\"umbrella body\">umbrella body.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Registering with the <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>Employers who need to do more than 100 checks a year can deal with their own applications if they <a href=\"/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/contact-criminal-records-bureau\" title=\"contact the CRB\">register with the <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr></a>. This costs £300, plus £5 for each additional &lsquo;counter signatory&rsquo; (people within an organisation who are allowed to handle <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> applications).</p>\n\n<p>Registered organisations must follow the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/CRB/about-the-crb/crb-cop\" title=\"CRB code of practice\"><abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> code of practice.</a></p>\n\n<h3>The e-Bulk service</h3>\n\n<p>Employers who need to do more than 1,500 checks a year can use the <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr>&rsquo;s e-Bulk service, which can help reduce costs and waiting times for <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> checks.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/CRB/about-the-crb/ebulk-guidance?view=Binary\" title=\"e-Bulk service guidance\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘e-Bulk service guidance’ (PDF, 106KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Checks on carers</h2>\n\n<p>Employers providing care services for adults - eg in a care home - can use a service called <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.isaadultfirst.co.uk/guidance.aspx/\" title=\"Adult First\">Adult First.</a></p>\n\n<p>This will confirm, usually within 2 days, if the applicant:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>can start work, as long as they&rsquo;re supervised</li>\n  <li>should wait for the results of an enhanced check</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>The service costs an extra £6.</p>\n\n<h2>Employers in Scotland or Northern Ireland</h2>\n\n<p>Employers in Scotland can get a criminal records check from <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.disclosurescotland.co.uk/apply/employers/\" title=\"Apply for a disclosure\">Disclosure Scotland,</a> while employers in Northern Ireland should go through <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.dojni.gov.uk/accessni\" title=\"Apply for a disclosure\">Access NI.</a></p>\n\n<h2>Overseas applicants</h2>\n\n<p>If the applicant is from overseas, the employer can ask their <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.fco.gov.uk/en/travel-and-living-abroad/foreign-embassies-in-uk/\" title=\"foreign embassy\">foreign embassy</a> if it can get a similar check done in their country.</p>\n\n<h2>Employing ex-offenders</h2>\n\n<p>If you carry out criminal records checks, you must have a policy on employing ex-offenders. You must show it to any applicant who asks for it.</p>\n\n<div class=\"form-download\">\n<p><a href=\"http://www.homeoffice.gov.uk/publications/agencies-public-bodies/CRB/about-the-crb/sample-policy-rec-exoffend?view=Binary\" title=\"Download 'Sample policy on the recruitment of ex-offenders' (PDF, 53KB)\" rel=\"external\">Download ‘Sample policy on the recruitment of ex-offenders’ (PDF, 53KB)</a></p>\n</div>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/crb-criminal-records-bureau-check/isa-barred-lists","slug":"isa-barred-lists","order":5,"title":"ISA barred lists","body":"<p>Jobs that involve caring for, supervising or being in sole charge of children or adults require an enhanced <abbr title=\"Criminal Records Bureau\">CRB</abbr> check. </p>\n\n<p>This includes checking whether someone is included in the 2 Independent Safeguarding Authority (<abbr title=\"Independent Safeguarding Authority\">ISA</abbr>) &lsquo;barred lists&rsquo; of individuals who are unsuitable for working with:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>children</li>\n  <li>adults</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div cla