 Allowance\">JSA</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>You can only claim contribution-based <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr> for 6 months - after this, you may still be able to get income-based <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>The amount you can get might go down if you have:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>earnings from part-time work</li>\n  <li>an occupational or personal pension</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Extra rules for income-based <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr></h2>\n\n<p>Usually, to qualify for income-based <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr>: </p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>your partner (if you have one) must work less than 24 hours a week on average</li>\n  <li>you and your partner must have less than £16,000 in savings</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Your household income can affect how much you get too. This includes money from savings (if you have £6,000 or more), pensions and earnings. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Use the <a href=\"/benefits-adviser\" title=\"Benefits adviser\">benefits adviser</a> to check your eligibility.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>16 to 17 years olds</h2>\n\n<p><abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr> isn’t usually paid to 16 or 17 year olds or people in full-time education, except in certain circumstances. Contact your local <a href=\"/contact-jobcentre-plus\" title=\"Get contact details for Jobcentre Plus\">Jobcentre Plus</a> for advice. </p>\n\n<h2>Your circumstances change</h2>\n\n<p>Tell Jobcentre Plus if your circumstances change as this can affect how much money you get. For example, you start working or your income changes. </p>\n\n<p>Volunteering won&rsquo;t normally affect your <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr> but you must report that you&rsquo;re doing it. </p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>To keep getting <abbr title=\"Jobseeker's Allowance\">JSA</abbr> you’ll normally have to attend a Jobcentre Plus every 2 weeks to show how your job search i