view</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t take compulsory steps that will help you find work, eg by attending a training course when you&rsquo;re told to</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t apply for or don&rsquo;t accept a place on an employment programme or  training scheme that you&rsquo;re told about</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t attend or take part in an employment programme or  training scheme, or leave voluntarily</li>\n  <li>lose  your place on an employment programme or  training scheme because of misconduct</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>You could lose your Jobseeker&rsquo;s Allowance for up to 3  years if you:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t apply for a job that your adviser tells you about</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t accept a suitable job offer</li>\n  <li>leave a job voluntarily, or lose your job because of misconduct</li>\n  <li>don&rsquo;t take part in a compulsory work activity programme</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice help-notice\">\n<p>Your benefit will stop and you’ll no longer be eligible for Jobseeker’s  Allowance if you don’t look or you’re not available for work.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>If your benefit is stopped</h2>\n\n<p>You must still go to your local Jobcentre Plus or  attend any employment programme you&rsquo;re on - otherwise you may lose your benefit for longer or altogether.</p>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>You may be able to claim hardship payments if you’re suffering financial hardship - speak to your adviser at your Jobcentre for more information.</p>\n</div>\n\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-11-01T12:22:14+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Jobseeker's Allowance and low income benefits","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/benefits%2Fjobseekers-allowance.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes Income Support, Community Care Grants and Crisis Loans","short_description":"","type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=benefits%2Fjobseekers-allowance","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/browse/benefits/jobseekers-allow