ork-choice/\" title=\"Work Choice\">Work Choice</a> - to help you find a job, and get support when you start work</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/residential-training/\" title=\"Residential Training\">Residential Training</a> - to give you work experience and training</li>\n  <li><a href=\"/access-to-work/\" title=\"Access to Work grants\">Access to Work</a> - money towards a support worker or for the cost of equipment or travelling to work</li>\n</ul>\n\n"},{"web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/looking-for-work-if-youre-disabled/applying-for-a-job","slug":"applying-for-a-job","order":2,"title":"Applying for a job","body":"<h2>Questions about your health or disability</h2>\n\n<p>An employer isn&rsquo;t normally allowed to ask you questions about your health or disability before they offer you a job.</p>\n\n<p>They can only ask you about this for very limited reasons, for example to:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>make &lsquo;reasonable adjustments&rsquo; - eg if you need a large print version of a test</li>\n  <li>decide if you can do something that is an essential part of the job</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>If you&rsquo;re treated unfairly when you apply for a job</h2>\n\n<p>Contact the <a href=\"/discrimination-your-rights/contact-the-equality-and-human-rights-commission/\" title=\"Equality and Human Rights Commission\">Equality and Human Rights Commission</a> if you think you&rsquo;ve been treated unfairly.</p>\n\n<p>You may also be able to take a complaint to an <a href=\"/employment-tribunals/\" title=\"employment tribunal\">employment tribunal</a> - you have to do this within 3 months of the discrimination happening.</p>\n"}]},"updated_at":"2012-11-18T14:28:01+00:00","tags":[{"title":"Finding a job","id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/tags/working%2Ffinding-job.json","web_url":null,"details":{"description":"Includes job search, volunteering, apprenticeships and job offers","short_description":null,"type":"section"},"content_with_tag":{"id":"https://www.gov.uk/api/with_tag.json?tag=working%2Ffinding-job"