ces</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>If they give a reference it:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>must be be fair and accurate - and can include details about workers&rsquo; performance and if they were sacked</li>\n  <li>can be brief - eg job title, salary and when the worker was employed</li>\n</ul>\n\n<div class=\"application-notice info-notice\">\n<p>Once the worker starts with a new employer they can ask to see a copy of a reference. They have no right to ask their previous employer.</p>\n</div>\n\n<h2>Bad references</h2>\n\n<p>If the worker thinks they&rsquo;ve been given an unfair or misleading reference, they may be able to claim damages in a court. The previous employer must be able to back up the reference - eg, by supplying examples of warning letters.</p>\n\n<p>Workers must be able to show that:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>it&rsquo;s misleading or inaccurate</li>\n  <li>they &lsquo;suffered a loss&rsquo; (eg a job offer was withdrawn)</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Workers can get legal advice - eg from <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.adviceguide.org.uk/\" title=\"Citizens Advice\">Citizens Advice.</a> They may also be able to get <a href=\"/legal-aid\" title=\"legal aid\">legal aid</a>.</p>\n\n<h2>Discrimination and unfair dismissal</h2>\n\n<p>Workers may also be able to claim damages from a court if:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>the employment contract says they must be given a reference, but the employer refuses to</li>\n  <li>the worker is sacked because they&rsquo;ve been asked to give a reference while the worker&rsquo;s still working for them</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>Workers can get legal advice - eg from <a rel=\"external\" href=\"http://www.adviceguide.org.uk/\" title=\"Citizens Advice\">Citizens Advice.</a> They may also be able to get <a href=\"/legal-aid\" title=\"Legal aid\">legal aid</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Contact <abbr title=\"Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service\">Acas</abbr> (Advisory, Conciliation and Arbitration Service) for advice:</p>\n\n<div class=\"contact\">\n<p><strong><abbr title=\"Advi